President Emmanuel Macron of France, Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany, Prime Minister Mario Draghi of Italy, Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom, and President Biden of the United States held a call to discuss their concerns about the Russian military build-up on Ukraine's borders and Russia's harsh rhetoric. They called on Russia to de-escalate tensions and emphasized the importance of diplomacy, particularly through the Normandy Format and the implementation of the Minsk Agreements, to resolve the conflict in Donbas. The leaders expressed their support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity and agreed to maintain close communication with NATO allies and EU partners.